=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex28 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 323 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 323.0297
  harmonic_decay_rate: -5.0960
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1291
  pitch_clarity: 22.7879
  inharmonicity: 0.2653
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -7.1739
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 28
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 28 ---
(
{
    var a, b;
    a = FSinOsc.ar(800);
    b = FSinOsc.ar(XLine.kr(200,500,5));
    (a * b) * 0.125
}.play)
